Such cases should be referred to the relevant authorities for approval,[152] (p8) a process that can take 7-60days while the health centres can only carry out abortions while following the woman's decision.[152] (p8

Due to this inefficiency, women also resort to obtaining illegal abortions using a surgical, chemical or manual method such as using knitting needles,[152] (p11 as have been reported in South Sudan[288] and Zimbabwe.[289] Termination of pregnancy also takes place abroad in refugee camps.[290]

This study by the IOM, which surveyed 2,384 sexually and/or physically abused women at health facilities in 293 communities
